<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10003b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10003b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10003b"> 3(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sithric m Brian&apos;s d.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Vikings in Ireland]</font>: The Leinstermen under King Maelmordha, dissatisfied with this arrangement <font color="green">[leaving Brian master of Leth Mogha (<i>i.e.</i> the southern half of Ireland)]</font>, began to make trouble and revolted, assisted by the Dublin Norsemen. An important victory was gained over their combined armies at Gleann Mama (Co. Wicklow) in the year 1000 by Brian, who after the battle captured Dublin. King Sihtric (O.N. Sigtrygger), son of Olaf Cuaran, had to submit to Brian&apos;s authority. Having accepted his allegiance Brian married Gormflaith, mother of Sihtric and sister of Maelmordha, and at the same time <mark>gave his own daughter to Sihtric in marriage</mark>. <small> A. WALSH, <a name="AWSR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AWSR"><cite title="source">Scandinavian Relations with Ireland During the Viking Period</cite></a> (1922) 8f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
